originalText.text: VERY cramped and tight spaces, your car will 10000% get hit here, mine already has been scraped by someone less than 1 week of parking here. There are no cameras. The corners to turn into a higher/lower level are 1 car wide which means it’s very hard to see if someone else is driving toward the corner and it’s dangerous.

originalText.text: Outstanding service!. Carlos in lot "B" took care of my car like it was his own.  They took pictures of the front and back of my vehicle before and checked it again when they returned it to me. I will ask for him again when I return.

originalText.text: It can be a bit daunting as you enter the facility. Pay attention and follow attendants directions. Your car will be valet parked outside. Parking is either $26 or $29. The cashiers can be abrupt. Don't mistake this as rude, they just want to keep things moving. All covid protections apply.

originalText.text: The valet at this garage damaged my car. He put a large scratch in the front bumper. I filed a complaint with the manager, Daisy Alequin, and I was told that I would receive an email response in 3-5 days. It has now been over a week with no response. It is very unfortunate that the employees at this garage have zero respect for their customers' property and attempt to ignore the damage they cause.

originalText.text: One of the front desk staff is unbelievably rude. A female office staff employee of African descent was utterly disgusting towards me.  She quickly and unnecessarily escalated the conversation by threatening to call security. Thankfully I am a board certified physician and I know how to handle interactions with mentally unstable individuals. This woman clearly was deranged and should not be allowed to have any contact with customers. I am thoroughly disappointed that I was treated this way at the #1 hospital in NYC. Please do better NYP.
